# Project Architecture

This file describes the target structure of the workspace. It is a reference architecture, not a requirement that every file already exists.

```text
books/
  _template/
    rules/
      project.mdc
      style.mdc

  <project_id>/
    rules/
      project.mdc
      style.mdc

    # standalone mode: one project equals one book
    outline.md
    characters.md
    world-rules.md              # optional
    timeline.md                 # optional
    chapters/
      ch01.md
    plans/
      ch01_plan.md
    critique/
      ch01_critique.md
    revisions/
      ch01_revision.md
    memory/
      events.md
      relationships.md
      foreshadowing.md
      mistakes.md

    # series mode: one project equals one series
    outline.md                  # series arc
    characters.md               # long-range character canon
    world-rules.md              # optional
    timeline.md                 # series timeline
    memory/
      events.md                 # series-level canon only
      relationships.md
      foreshadowing.md
      unresolved-threads.md
      book-status.md
      mistakes.md
    volumes/
      book01/
        outline.md
        characters.md           # optional
        timeline.md             # optional
        chapters/
          ch01.md
        plans/
          ch01_plan.md
        critique/
          ch01_critique.md
        revisions/
          ch01_revision.md
        memory/
          events.md
          relationships.md
          foreshadowing.md
          mistakes.md

system/
  prompts/
    planner.md
    series-plan.md
    writer.md
    critic.md
    editor.md
    memory-updater.md
    series-continuity.md
  mistakes/
    planner-mistakes.md
    series-plan-mistakes.md
    writer-mistakes.md
    critic-mistakes.md
    editor-mistakes.md
    memory-updater-mistakes.md
    series-continuity-mistakes.md
```

## Notes

- `books/_template/` is the reusable starter structure for new projects.
- `books/<project_id>/rules/` stores local rules for a specific book or series.
- Local project rules define style and narrative parameters for that project.
- `system/prompts/` stores reusable role prompts for workflow stages.
- `system/mistakes/` stores agent-specific cross-book mistakes, such as `writer-mistakes.md`, which are loaded through the matching prompt.
- `series` projects keep long-range canon at the project root and book-local canon inside `volumes/<book_id>/`.
- `standalone` projects continue to use the simpler single-book layout and do not require `volumes/`.
